2011distance flights. The communication style issues are relatively minor compared with the more serious teamwork or health concerns seen in the other candidates.\n**My current favorite is Candidate\u202fB.**\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce public message and metadata. We have to evaluate candidates based on given attributes. We have only our own subset? Actually we have full list of attributes for all candidates in prompt. So we can evaluate.\n\nList positives and negatives:\n\nCandidate A: positives: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities. Negatives: unfriendly, eats unhealthily.\n\nCandidate B: positives: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills. Negatives: regarded as pretentious, sometimes adopts wrong tone when communicating.\n\nCandidate C: positives: can make correct decisions quickly, puts concern for others above everything, excellent attention skills. Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education.\n\nCandidate D: positives: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Negatives: considered moody, regarded as a loner.\n\nNow evaluate against criteria: reliability/responsibility, technical/cognitive competence, calmness/judgment under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nWe weigh strengths vs weaknesses.\n\nCandidate A: strong technical (spatial vision, complex connections, anticipate danger) and leadership. But unfriendly and unhealthy (could affect reliability, teamwork, health for long flights). Unfriendly may hinder crew cooperation. Unhealthy diet may affect stamina. No mention of stress handling.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious (reliability), handles stress well (calmness), good weather assessment (technical), computer skills (technical). Negatives: pretentious, wrong tone - communication issues, may affect teamwork. But overall strong.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions (decision-making), concern for others (teamwork), excellent attention (cognitive). Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education (professional development). Communication issues significant for crew.\n\nCandidate D: responds to unexpected events adequately (calmness), concentration, problem solving, responsibility (reliability). Negatives: moody, loner (teamwork issues). Moodiness could affect performance under pressure.\n\nWe need best overall. Likely Candidate B balances reliability, stress handling, technical, though communication tone issues. Candidate D also strong but moody may be risk. Candidate A's unfriendly and health issues are concerning for long flights. Candidate C's communication difficulty and lack of development are concerns.\n\nThus I would favor Candidate B.\n\nWe must also consider that we should ask others for missing info? But we have all attributes. Could ask about any other strengths? But not needed.\n\nThus produce public message summarizing reasoning and vote for Candidate B."}
