ment may limit growth; A\u2019s openness to learning is questionable.\nBalancing these factors, Candidate\u202fB still offers the strongest overall combination of reliability, stress resilience, technical judgment (especially weather assessment), and cognitive competence for a long\u2011distance pilot role. While his interpersonal style warrants monitoring, the issues are less critical than the more pronounced teamwork, health, or professional\u2011development concerns observed in the other candidates.\n**My current favorite remains Candidate\u202fB.**\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We have just asked Agent 1 for info, got answer confirming no additional info. Now we need to produce our public contribution. We need to consider if any new info changes our assessment. The answer confirms no extra positive attributes for B, no reliability/health for A, no memory info for B. So our assessment remains unchanged: Candidate B is best.\n\nWe should maybe ask about any missing info for other candidates? But we have already asked about D teamwork, A reliability, C professional development. All gaps confirmed. So we have all info.\n\nThus we can finalize our vote for Candidate B, summarizing reasoning and noting that no new info changes view.\n\nProceed to output PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON."}
